The cheapness of brochures allows them to be distributed in large quantities and thereby combat illiteracy and popularize reading among the Brazilian population, which plays an important role in the development of education. Unfortunately, today Brazilian schools underestimate the role of this literature in the educational process[11]. historical events and political moods in society. Thus, during the election campaign in the fall of 2018, Thiau Simpatia wrote a curdel “In Brazil Bolsonaro”, where he raised the question of the future of his nation if Bolsonaro becomes the president of the country[13]. In addition, brochures were brought tourists to other parts of the world.